def gridfilter(intgrid):
    
    down=[];up=[];left=[];right=[]
    for i, eachline in enumerate(intgrid):
        for j, each in enumerate(eachline):
            if each==1:
                down.append([[j,j+1],[i,i]])
                up.append([[j,j+1],[i+1,i+1]])
                left.append([[j,j],[i,i+1]])
                right.append([[j+1,j+1],[i,i+1]])
        
    together=[]
    for each in down: together.append(each)
    for each in up: together.append(each)
    for each in left: together.append(each)
    for each in right: together.append(each)
        
        
    filtered=[]
    for each in together:
        c=0
        for EACH in together:
            if each==EACH:
                c+=1
        if c==1:
            filtered.append(each)
        
    return filtered

class star:
    
    def __init__(self, ID):
        
        self.ID = ID
        
        with open(glob.glob("*"+str(self.ID)+"*gridout*")[0]) as fin:
            fin.readline()
            self.grid=[i.split() for i in fin.readlines()]

        for index, each in enumerate(self.grid):
            for INDEX, EACH in enumerate(each):
                self.grid[index][INDEX]=int(EACH)
        
        with open(glob.glob("*"+str(self.ID)+"*value*")[0]) as fin:
            self.threshold=float(fin.readlines()[1])
        
        
        self.booleangrid=np.asarray(self.grid)>self.threshold
        
        self.labelgrid, self.num_features = scipy.ndimage.measurements.label(self.booleangrid)      
        sizeoffeature=0
        self.largestfeature=0
        self.featuresizelist=[]
        
        for i in range(self.num_features):
        
            sizeofthis=len(np.where(self.labelgrid == (i+1))[0])

            self.featuresizelist.append(sizeofthis)
            
            if sizeofthis>sizeoffeature:
                
                sizeoffeature=sizeofthis
                self.largestfeature=(i+1)
                
                
        self.chosenap = self.labelgrid == self.largestfeature
        self.intgrid=self.chosenap*1
        self.filtered=gridfilter(self.intgrid)        
                
        with open(glob.glob("/home/pal/konkoly/automaticaperture/sourcefits/*"+str(self.ID)+"*kepmask")[0]) as f:
            maskfile = f.read()
        f.closed
        cords=maskfile.split("|")[5]
        cordlist=cords.split(";")
        
        cordlistmat=[]
        for index, line in enumerate(cordlist):
            cordlistmat.append(line.split(","))
        
        cordlistmat_tofloats=[]
        for line in(cordlistmat):
            cordlistmat_tofloats.append([int(line[0]),int(line[1])])
        
        cordlistmat_inrange=[]
        for line in cordlistmat_tofloats:
            if 0<=line[0] and line[0]<10 and 0<=line[1] and line[1]<10:
                cordlistmat_inrange.append(line)
                
        attilamask_x=[];attilamask_y=[]
        for each in cordlistmat_inrange:
            attilamask_x.append(each[0])
            attilamask_y.append(each[1])
                        
                
        self.attilaaper=[]
        for x in range(len(self.grid)):
            sublist=[]
            for y in range(len(self.grid[0])):
                sublist.append(0)
            self.attilaaper.append(sublist)
    
        for each in cordlistmat_inrange:
            self.attilaaper[each[0]][each[1]]=1
            
        self.attilafiltered=gridfilter(self.attilaaper)
In [4]:
def findgaps(times, mingap = .5):
    ret=[]
    t=times[0]
    for i in range(1, len(times)):
        if times[i]-t >= mingap:
            ret.append(i)
        t=times[i]
    ret.append(len(times))
    return ret

def simit(data, blocksize = 500, order = 1):
    outliers_free = data; # matrix without outliers
    
    apdix = numpy.array([])
    curve1 = numpy.copy(data)
    
    
    if len(outliers_free) <= 2*blocksize:
        corr = numpy.ones((len(outliers_free)))*numpy.average(outliers_free[:,1])
    else:
        smcurve = numpy.zeros(shape=(int(len(outliers_free)/blocksize)+2,2))
        for i in range(1, int(len(outliers_free)/blocksize)+1):
            smcurve[i] = [numpy.average(outliers_free[blocksize*(i-1):blocksize*(i),0]),numpy.average(outliers_free[blocksize*(i-1):blocksize*(i),1])]
        smcurve[0,0] = outliers_free[0,0]
        smcurve[-1,0] = outliers_free[-1,0]
        smcurve[0,1] = smcurve[1,1]-(smcurve[1,0]-smcurve[0,0])*(smcurve[2,1]-smcurve[1,1])/(smcurve[2,0]-smcurve[1,0])
        smcurve[-1,1] = smcurve[-2,1]+(smcurve[-1,0]-smcurve[-2][0])*(smcurve[-2][1]-smcurve[-3][1])/(smcurve[-2][0]-smcurve[-3][0])

        corrfunction = scipy.interpolate.interp1d(smcurve[:,0], smcurve[:,1], order)
        
        corr = corrfunction(curve1[:,0])
        
    for i in range(len(curve1)):
        print ('{:11.6f}  {:7.3f} {:8.6f}'.format(curve1[i,0], \
        curve1[i,1], curve1[i,2],
        corr[i]/numpy.average(outliers_free[:,1])))
        
        return curve1, corr

bls=500
ordr=3
mngp=.5  

for index, each in enumerate(readytolaunchIDs):
    #lc = numpy.loadtxt(each,skiprows=4)
    lc = numpy.loadtxt(glob.glob("*"+str(list(readytolaunchIDs)[index])+"*"+"OOPoutII")[0], skiprows=4)
    flags = numpy.zeros(( len(lc),1 ))
    #sigmaclipped=astropy.stats.sigma_clip(lc[:,1],4)
    #flags = np.asarray([each*1 for each in sigmaclipped.mask.tolist()])

    sigmaclipped=astropy.stats.sigma_clip(lc[:,1],2)
    flags2 = numpy.asarray([[float(each*1)] for each in sigmaclipped.mask.tolist()])
    flags2 = numpy.asarray(flags2)
    flags = flags2
    
    
    lc = numpy.hstack(( lc,flags ))
    lc = lc[lc[:,2] == 0]
    lcf = lc[~numpy.isnan(lc[:, 1])]
    boundaries=findgaps(lcf[:,0], mingap = mngp)
    fr = 0
    for i in boundaries:# cycle above the number of gaps
        curve1, corr = simit(lcf[fr:i, :], blocksize = bls, order = ordr)
        fr = i
    isthisspline=np.asarray(corr)/np.mean(curve1[:,1])
    plt.figure(figsize=(12,5))
    plt.plot(curve1[:,1]/isthisspline)
    plt.xlabel("BJD")
    plt.ylabel("AUTOAPER-K2SC-3SIGMACLIPPED-SPLINED LC")
    plt.title(str(each))
    #plt.plot(curve1[:,1],c='red',linewidth=1)
    #plt.ylim([2500,4200])
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.figure()
    
    plt.plot(isthisspline)
    plt.xlabel("BJD")
    plt.ylabel("SPLINE")
    
    
    
    
    ourstar=star(each)

    plt.figure()
    plt.pcolormesh(ourstar.grid)
    plt.xlabel("RED: AUTOAPER, BLACK: HANDMADE, COLOR: Ns PIXEL WAS CHOSEN TO FORM APER")
    for x in range(len(ourstar.filtered)):
        plt.plot(ourstar.filtered[x][0],ourstar.filtered[x][1],c='red', linewidth=9)

    for x in range(len(ourstar.attilafiltered)):
        plt.plot(ourstar.attilafiltered[x][0],ourstar.attilafiltered[x][1],c='black',linewidth=6)
        
    plt.figure(figsize=(200,1))
    plt.plot()
    ax = plt.gca()
    ax.set_facecolor('xkcd:black')
    ax.set_xticklabels([])
    ax.set_yticklabels([])
